    <h1>Privacy Policy for Word Imposter</h1>
    <p class="effective-date"><strong>Effective Date:</strong> 10 August 2025</p>

    <p>Word Imposter (“the App”, “we”, “our”, or “us”) respects your privacy and is committed to protecting it. This Privacy Policy describes the types of information we may collect, how it is used, and the choices you have regarding your information.</p>

    <h2>1. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We currently do <strong>not</strong> collect or store any personal information from our users. The only information handled by the App is temporary game-related data necessary for gameplay, such as:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Game session data</li>
        <li>Player nicknames (as chosen by the player)</li>
        <li>Game state information (e.g., scores, round progress)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>This data is processed temporarily and is deleted daily.</p>
    <p><strong>If analytics are enabled in the future</strong>, the App may also collect non-personal usage data, such as:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Device type and operating system</li>
        <li>App version</li>
        <li>General usage statistics (e.g., number of games played)</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>2. Third-Party Services</h2>
    <p>The App may use third-party services for advertisements, analytics, or similar functionality. These services may collect information in accordance with their own privacy policies.</p>
    <p>Possible third-party services include (but are not limited to):</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Google AdMob</strong> – for displaying ads</li>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics for Firebase</strong> – for anonymous usage analytics</li>
        <li><strong>Firebase Crashlytics</strong> – for error reporting</li>
    </ul>
    <p>These services may collect information such as:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Device identifiers</li>
        <li>Approximate location (non-precise)</li>
        <li>Interaction with ads</li>
        <li>General usage statistics</li>
    </ul>
    <p>You can review their privacy policies here:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google AdMob & Firebase Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://firebase.google.com/support/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Firebase Privacy and Security</a></li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. Children’s Privacy</h2>
    <p>The App is designed for players aged 10 and above. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If you believe we have inadvertently collected such information, please contact us and we will delete it promptly.</p>

    <h2>4. Data Security</h2>
    <p>We take reasonable measures to protect the information processed by the App. Game-related data is only used for gameplay and is not stored beyond the active session.</p>

    <h2>5. Your Choices</h2>
    <p>If the App includes ads or analytics in the future, you may be able to opt out of personalized advertising by adjusting your device settings:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Android:</strong> Settings → Google → Ads → Opt out of Ads Personalization</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p>We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted within the App and/or on our official website, with the “Effective Date” updated accordingly.</p>

    <h2>7. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have any questions about this Privacy Policy or our practices, you can contact us at:</p>
    <p>contact.a59.dev@gmail.com</p>
